Once an administrative hearing is requested or scheduled, the proceeding shall be governed by the District of Columbia Administrative Procedure Act, approved October 4, 1968, as amended (82 Stat. 1203; D.C. Official Code §§ 2-501 to 2-510 (2001));
      the Office of Administrative Hearings Establishment Act of 2001, effective March 6, 2002 (D.C. Law 14-76; D.C. Official Code §§ 2-1831.01 to 2-1831.19 (2001)); and the rules of practice and procedure established by the District of Columbia Office
      of Administrative Hearings (OAH) in chapters 28 and 29 of Title 1 of the District of Columbia Municipal Regulations (1 DCMR).
